{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-classic-show-tsx","path":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-101-to-200/problem-106-special-subset-sums-meta-testing","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"block":"project-euler-problems-101-to-200","demoType":null,"title":"Vežba 106: Posebne tvrdnje za podskupove: Meta-verifikacija","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>Neka $S(A)$ predstavlja ukupan broj elemenata u skupu A sa veličinom n. Nazvaćemo ga specijalnim skupom unije ako su za dva disjunktna podskupa, B i C, sledeća svojstva tačna:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>$S(B) ≠ S(C)$; odnosno, zbi za manje skupove ne mogu biti jednaki.</li>\n<li>Ako B ima više elemenata nego C, onda $S(B) > S(C)$.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Za ovaj izazov, pretpostavljamo da dati set ima elemente $n$ koji rastu po koraku i već zadovoljava drugo pravilo.</p>\n<p>Iznenada, od 25 mogućih skupa podskupova koji se mogu dobiti iz skupa sa n = 4, samo jedan skup zahteva proveru jednakosti (prvi princip). Slično tome, kada je n = 7, samo 70 skupa od 966 podskupova zahteva proveru.</p>\n<p>Za n = 12, koliko skupova među dostupnim podskupovima od 261625 treba proveriti na jednakost?</p>\n<p><strong>Napomena:</strong> Ovaj izazov je povezan sa Vežbom 103 i Vežbom 105.</p>\n</section>","id":"5900f3d71000cf542c50fee9","hasEditableBoundaries":false,"instructions":"","notes":null,"challengeType":1,"helpCategory":"Euler","videoUrl":null,"superBlock":"project-euler","translationPending":false,"forumTopicId":301730,"hooks":null,"fields":{"slug":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-101-to-200/problem-106-special-subset-sums-meta-testing"},"required":[],"usesMultifileEditor":false,"challengeFiles":[{"fileKey":"scriptjs","ext":"js","name":"script","contents":"function subsetSumsMetaTesting() {\n\n  return true;\n}\n\nsubsetSumsMetaTesting();","head":null,"tail":null,"editableRegionBoundaries":[],"history":["script.js"]}],"saveSubmissionToDB":null,"tests":[{"text":"<p><code>subsetSumsMetaTesting()</code> trebalo bi da vrati <code>21384</code>.</p>","testString":"assert.strictEqual(subsetSumsMetaTesting(), 21384);"}]}}},"pageContext":{"challengeMeta":{"blockHashSlug":"/learn/project-euler/#project-euler-problems-101-to-200","dashedName":"problem-106-special-subset-sums-meta-testing","certification":"project-euler","disableLoopProtectTests":true,"disableLoopProtectPreview":true,"superBlock":"project-euler","chapter":null,"module":null,"block":"project-euler-problems-101-to-200","isFirstStep":false,"template":null,"required":[],"isLastChallengeInBlock":false,"nextChallengePath":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-101-to-200/problem-107-minimal-network","prevChallengePath":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-101-to-200/problem-105-special-subset-sums-testing","id":"5900f3d71000cf542c50fee9","saveSubmissionToDB":null},"projectPreview":{"challengeData":{"challengeType":1,"challengeFiles":[{"name":"script","ext":"js","contents":"// solution required","history":["script.js"],"fileKey":"scriptjs"}]}},"id":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-101-to-200/problem-106-special-subset-sums-meta-testing"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3858520367"],"slicesMap":{}}